station-event-deathsquad-enroute = All contracts with crew have been terminated. Royal Guard is to lay down arms, and former crew are required to surrender to Equestria. Failure to do so will result in capital punishment. Command is to peacefully surrender first, to set an example for the former crew.
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-generic-enroute = Emergency Response Team enroute. Glory to Equestria.
station-event-cburn-enroute = A biological threat or virus has deemed it necessary to deploy a CBURN ERT. Crew is heavily advised to quarantine themselves and others, ponyville hospital department is suggested to bolt their doors unless told otherwise by Command staff or members of the ERT. Crewmembers and Cleaning Ponys are advised to wear bio-suits, protective masks, and gloves to prevent the risk of viruses spreading
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-engineering-enroute = A structural issue that cannot be easily contained on your ponyville has been brought to our attention. An Cloudsmithing ERT has been deployed to deal with said issue, Cloudsmithing ERT members are now officially above the Rainbow Dash and Celestia when dealing with the structural issue."
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-security-enroute = Canterlot has deemed the situation fit enough to qualify for a team of 5 ERT Royal Guard Members outfitted with Annies. The chain of command is officially updated so that ERT members are above celestia while they are deployed. Civilians are to standby and allow ERT, Command, and Royal Guard to deal with the threat(s).
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-medical-enroute = A mass-causality has deemed it fit to deploy a Ponyville Hospital ERT. Ponyville Hospital's command structure has been updated to make deployed Ponyville Hospital ERT members above the Fluttershy, and the Celestia in ponyville hospital situations. Members of the ERT and Ponyville Hospital are suggested to work together, members of the ERT should remain in ponyville hospital unless it becomes unsafe or crowded.
